hs (c) (1) through (14). (6) For all substantial improvements to existing construction within Zones AR/A1&hyph;30, AR/AE, AR/AH, AR/AO, and AR/A: (i) Determine the A1&hyph;30 or AE, AH, AO, or A Zone base flood elevation; and (ii) Using this elevation apply the requirements of paragraphs (c)(1) through (c)(14). (7) Notify the permit applicant that the area has been designated as an AR, AR/A1&hyph;30, AR/AE, AR/AH, AR/AO, or AR/A Zone and whether the structure will be elevated or protected to or above the AR base flood elevation. PART 64_COMMUNITIES ELIGIBLE FOR THE SALE OF INSURANCE 7. The authority citation for Part 64 is revised to read as follows: Authority: 42 U.S.C. 4001 et seq.; Reorganization Plan No. 3 of 1978, 3 CFR, 1978 Comp., p. 329; E.O. 12127, 3 CFR, 1979 Comp., p. 376. 8. Section 64.3 is amended by adding an ``AR'' entry in the chart in paragraph (a)(1) after the ``AH'' entry and revising paragraph (b) to read as follows: ยง64.3 Flood Insurance Maps.
